data.title: Kiev court victory in Quinn case
data.meta_description: The state-owned Irish Bank Resolution Corporation (IBRC) has registered its first significant victory in Ukraine’s courts, a week after a government minister held talks with the Ukrainian government
data.text:
The state-owned Irish Bank Resolution Corporation (IBRC) has registered its first significant victory in Ukraine’s courts, a week after a government minister held talks with the Ukrainian government in an attempt to secure the assets of the Quinn International Property Group (IPG).

IBRC, the former Anglo Irish Bank, won an injunction last week protecting its €52m mortgage on the Leonardo office tower block in Kiev, the Ukrainian capital.

The bank has struggled for two years to vindicate its interests in €130m of former IPG property in Kiev — the €70m Leonardo business centre, and Ukraina, a €60m shopping centre with an annual rental yield of €10m.
